casebody.data:
Tuesday, February 18, 1992

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

91-2146. Wax v. Limbach.

Board of Tax Appeals, No. 90-J-513. This cause, here on appeal from the Board of Tax Appeals, was considered in the manner prescribed by law. Upon consideration of appellant’s application to dismiss,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said application be, and the same is hereby, granted, effective February 13, 1992.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
